---------------------------- MODULE II_006 ----------------------------
\* GENERATED by the TLC-SL compiler from II-006 — Activate prior knowledge before new instruction.
\* Article Instructional Integrity / Merrill First Principles. Enforcement WARN.
\* STATUS: emitted, NOT yet checked by TLC in this build. See tla.mjs header.
EXTENDS TLC

VARIABLES activation, instruction
vars == << activation, instruction >>

TypeOK ==
  /\ activation \in { "none", "done" }
  /\ instruction \in { "not_started", "started" }

Init ==
  /\ activation = "none"
  /\ instruction = "not_started"

Op_ACTIVATE_PRIOR_KNOWLEDGE ==
  /\ TRUE
  /\ activation' = "done"
  /\ UNCHANGED << instruction >>

Op_BEGIN_INSTRUCTION ==
  /\ (activation = "done")
  /\ instruction' = "started"
  /\ UNCHANGED << activation >>

Next ==
  \/ Op_ACTIVATE_PRIOR_KNOWLEDGE
  \/ Op_BEGIN_INSTRUCTION

Spec == Init /\ [][Next]_vars

\* Safety property (Constitution Instructional Integrity / Merrill First Principles):
Safety == ((instruction = "started") => (activation = "done"))
